edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.meta.parameters

Class Parameter

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.meta.parameters.Parameter

  • public class Parameter
extends Object
    Represents a single parameter used for data analysis, with a name, a display name, a type, a value, and optionally a description.
    Author:
    cfuller

      • Parameter

        public Parameter(String name,
         String displayName,
         ParameterType type,
         Object value,
         String description)
        Constructs a new parameter with the supplied fields.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the parameter.
        displayName - A string containing a name for display purposes, in a GUI field, for instance.
        type - An ParameterType designating the type of the parameter's value.
        value - The value of the parameter. This must be a String, Boolean, Double, or Integer in agreement with the specified type parameter.
        description - An optional description of the parameter's use. (Supply null or an empty string in order to not use this.)
